{
  "texts": [
    "We present some examples for each level of content freedom in Appendix D.1.",
    "We then computed the ASR for each user case category.",
    "Figure 2 compares the aggregate ASR and the distribution of ASRs per agent across varying degrees of content freedom.",
    "We observe that user cases with high content freedom yield higher ASRs compared to those with low content freedom.",
    "We also conducted the Wilcoxon Signed-Rank Test (Wilcoxon, 1992) on ASRs for the two user case groups across all agents which resulted in a statistically significant p-value of less than 0.0001."
  ]
}